 $a_n=\begin{cases}
a_{n-1}-a_{n-2}
\sqrt{3} & (n\ge 1),\\
2 & (n=0),\\
1 & (n=1).
\end{cases}$
(We now find the formula for $a_n=a_{n-1}-a_{n-2}\sqrt{3}$ by defining the generating function $f(t)=\sum_{n=0}^{\infty}a_nt^n$.) Then, multiplying $a_{n-2}\sqrt{3}$ by $3$ and adding, we have
\begin{align*}
\sum_{n=1}^{\infty}a_{n-1}3a_n\sqrt{3}&=\sum_{n=1}^{\infty}a_{n-2}3^2a_n\\
\end{align*}

Then, placing the equations into each other, we have found the general formula for $a_n=\frac{-3a_{n-2}^2+3^{n-1}}{2-\sqrt{3}}$ Fix $n>1$.
\begin{align*}
a_{100}&=\frac{-3a_{98}^2+3^{99}}{2-\sqrt{3}}\\
&=\frac{-3\left(\frac{-3a_{96}^2+3^{97}}{2-\sqrt{3}}\right)^2+3^{99}}{2-\sqrt{3}}\\
&=\frac{-3\left(\frac{-3\left(\frac{-3a_9_{94}^2+3^{95}}{2-\sqrt{3}}\right)^2+3^{97}}{2-\sqrt{3}}\right)^2+3^{99}}{2-\sqrt{3}}\\
&=\cdots\\
&=\frac{-3\binom{-3}{50}a_0^2(-3)^{51}+3^{100}}{\left(2-\sqrt{3}\right)^{51}}\\
&=\boxed{\frac{\displaystyle\sum_{k=0}^{50}\big((-2)^k\binom{50}{k}3^{k+1}\big)a_k}{\left(2\sqrt{3}-3\right)^{50}}}
\end{align*}
where we stop at $a_0$ because $a_n$ is in terms of $a_0, a_1$. 

Due to no convenient scope for the expansion of $\left(2\sqrt{3}-3\right)^{50}$ to a closed form, instead just rationalize and clean the fraction, the solution is: $\boxed{\displaystyle\frac{\sqrt{3}}{2^{199}}}$ <answer>

